Assignment 5 - Part 2

How to do it?:

  • Open the Rmarkdown file of this assignment (link) in Rstudio.

  • Right under each question, insert a code chunk (you can use the hotkey Ctrl + Alt + I to add a code chunk) and code the solution for the question.

  • Knit the rmarkdown file (hotkey: Ctrl + Alt + K) to export an html.

  • Publish the html file to your Githiub Page.

Submission: Submit the link on Github of the assignment to Canvas under Assignment 5 - Extra Credits.

  1. Download the c2015 dataset to your computer at this link. Load the library readxl (library(readxl)) then use the function read_excel() to read the c2015 dataset. The data is from Fatality Analysis Reporting System (FARS). The data includes vital accidents information, such as when, where, and how the accident happened. FARS also includes the drivers and passengers information, such as age,gender etc. Some of the fatal accident had multiple vehicles involved. More information about FARS can be found at: https://www.nhtsa.gov/research-data/fatality-analysis-reporting-system-fars

  1. Still with variable SEX. There are missing values in this variables that are not NAs. Identy the forms of missing values in this variable. Change all the forms of missing values to NAs.
df <- replace(df, df == 'Unknown' |
                  df == 'Missing' |
                  df == 'Not Available', NA)
  1. Still with variable SEX. After all the missing values are in the NAs form. Change the missing values of this variable to the majority sex.
majority_SEX = names(which.max(table(df$SEX)))
df$SEX = replace_na(df$SEX)

  • Use na_if to change all the forms of missing values to NAs
df = df %>% mutate(TRAV_SP = na_if(TRAV_SP, "Not Rep"))

df = df %>% mutate(TRAV_SP = na_if(TRAV_SP, "Unknown"))

df = df %>% mutate(TRAV_SP = na_if(TRAV_SP, "Stopped"))
  • Check the type of this variable using class. Use as.numeric to change the type to numeric.
class(df$TRAV_SP)
## [1] "character"
df$TRAV_SP = as.numeric(df$TRAV_SP)
  • Use replace_na to replace the NAs to the median of the variable.
df$TRAV_SP = as.numeric(df$TRAV_SP)

median_TRAV_SP = median(df$TRAV_SP, na.rm = TRUE)

df$TRAV_SP = replace_na(df$TRAV_SP, median_TRAV_SP)
  1. Find the correlation between Age of the drivers and Travel speed (TRAV_SP). Hint: You want to look at the seat positions (SEAT_POS variable) to filter out the observations about the drivers, then calculate the correlation.
df  %>% 
    filter(SEAT_POS == "Front Seat, Left Side") %>% 
    summarise(correlation = cor(df$TRAV_SP, df$AGE, use = "complete.obs"))
